Subject: Re: Use postprocessing to project internal signals. (PR#104)

The following is the one without syntax errors. Since the signal 'b' in the 
module 'buf' is an internal signal, it won't be projected out. 
module inv0;

input x = {true};
output y = {false,<1,2>};

process inv0;
*[ [x-]; y+; [x+]; y- ]
endprocess
endmodule


//-------------------------------
module inv1;
input x = {false};
output y = {true,<1,2>};

process inv1;
*[ [x+]; y-; [x-]; y+ ]
endprocess
endmodule

//-------------------------------
module  inv2;
input x = {false};
output y = {true,<1,2>};

process inv2;
*[ y+; [x+]; y-; [x-] ]
endprocess
endmodule


//--------------------------------
module buf;
input a;

inv1 i1(x => a, y => b);
inv0 i2(x => b, y => c);

endmodule

module main;

input Y;

buf A(a => X, c => Y);
inv2 B(x => Y, y => X);

endmodule
